## Fix
tests/integrations/conftest.py, two session autouse fixtures:
- clickhouse_traffic_bypasses_vcr: subclasses urllib3 HTTP(S)ConnectionPool
  with ConnectionCls pinned to the import-time real connection classes
  (shadows vcr's base-class ConnectionCls patch), sets
  manager.pool_classes_by_scheme on every clickhouse-connect pool manager
  (the module singleton + any from get_pool_manager, patched on BOTH httputil
  and httpclient since httpclient binds the name at import), and clears() so
  pre-existing pools rebuild immune. Result: CH traffic never enters VCR.
- httpcore_stays_patched_during_vcr_passthrough: monkeypatches
  vcr.patch.reset_patchers to drop the httpcore ConnectionPool/AsyncConnectionPool
  entries (matched via patcher.getter()). httpcore stubs don't use force_reset
  for their own passthrough, so removing them from the reset set is safe and
  closes the unpatch window for any residual urllib3 passthrough.
tests/integrations/langchain/test_vcr_isolation.py: two vcr-marked tests that
make no HTTP calls, only assert patch state under an active cassette. Both fail
deterministically with the conftest fix stashed (verified by stash/pop on amd64).
AGENTS.md: added "VCR + ClickHouse isolation" subsection.

