## Hints for Future Agents
- A real provider 4xx/429 under record_mode="none" means VCR's patches were
  ABSENT when the request fired - an isolation/timing bug - NOT a cassette
  mismatch. Cassette mismatches raise CannotOverwriteExistingCassetteException.
- vcr.patch._HttpcoreConnectionPool_handle_request is the import-time original;
  comparing httpcore.ConnectionPool.handle_request against it tells you if a
  cassette is currently patching httpcore. The regression test relies on this.
- To repro GH-runner timing locally: docker run --platform linux/amd64
  python:3.10, socat TCP-LISTEN:8123 -> host CH, mirror test.yaml env, loop the
  shard. Native arm64/macOS is too fast to repro.
- These fixtures touch private clickhouse-connect internals (_default_pool_manager,
  pool_classes_by_scheme) and private vcrpy internals (reset_patchers, patcher
  .getter()). If clickhouse-connect or vcrpy is upgraded and these tests break,
  that's the signal to revisit; the regression tests import the private names so
  a rename fails loudly at collection.

## Codebase Discoveries
- The trace_server marker is auto-applied in tests/trace_server/conftest.py
  pytest_collection_modifyitems to any test in a trace_server path OR using the
  trace_server fixture; the langchain tests get it via the client fixture.
- weave client flushes traces to CH from background threads (future_executor)
  during tests, so CH HTTP overlaps provider HTTP in wall-clock time - that
  overlap is the necessary condition for the race.

